19/09/2006
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Vice-Admiral Gheorghe Marin, the country's new chief of General Staff, announced plans Monday (18 September) to send another 190 Romanian soldiers to Afghanistan. 
The decision was made in response to a call from NATO for an additional 2,500 troops to counter a resurgence of violence in southern Afghanistan. 
Romania has 586 troops deployed already. 
(AP, Reuters - 18/09/06)
